label: applies to part
description: part, aspect, or form of the item to which the claim applies

label: applies to part
description: part, aspect, or form of the item to which the claim applies

label: applies to part
description: part, aspect, or form of the item to which the claim applies

label: applies to part
description: part, aspect, or form of the item to which the claim applies

label: start time
description: time an entity begins to exist or a statement starts being valid

label: end time
description: moment when an entity ceases to exist and a statement stops being entirely valid or no longer be true

label: point in time
description: date something took place, existed or a statement was true; for providing time use the "refine date" property (P4241)

label: of (DEPRECATED)
description: (Do not use. Find alternatives at WD:P642) qualifier stating that a statement applies within the scope of a particular item

label: statement is subject of
description: (qualifying) item that describes the relation identified in this statement

label: applies to jurisdiction
description: the item (institution, law, public office, public register, etc) or statement belongs to or has power over or applies to the value (a territorial jurisdiction: a country, state, municipality, etc)

label: criterion used
description: property by which a distinction or classification is made

label: replaced by
description: other person or item which continues the item by replacing it in its role. Use P156 ("followed by") if the item is not replaced nor identical, but adds to the series (e.g. books in a series).

label: earliest date
description: earliest date at which an event could have happened. Use as qualifier for other date properties

label: latest date
description: latest possible time that something could have occurred. Use as qualifier for other date properties

label: replaces
description: person, state or item replaced. Use "structure replaces" (P1398) for structures. Use "follows" (P155) if the previous item was not replaced or predecessor and successor are identical

label: series ordinal
description: position of an item in its parent series (most frequently a 1-based index), generally to be used as a qualifier (different from "rank" defined as a class, and from "ranking" defined as a property for evaluating a quality)

label: together with
description: qualifier to specify the item that this property is shared with

label: subject named as
description: name by which a subject is recorded in a database, mentioned as a contributor of a work, or is referred to in a particular context

label: reason for deprecated rank
description: qualifier to indicate why a particular statement should have deprecated rank

label: object of statement has role
description: (qualifier) role held by the predicate value (object) of a statement in the context of that statement; for the role of the item the statement appears on (subject), use P2868

label: nature of statement
description: (qualifier only) the underlying circumstances of this statement

label: reason for preferred rank
description: qualifier to allow the reason to be indicated why a particular statement should be considered preferred
